# .gitleaksignore — fingerprints of known false-positive findings.
#
# Each line is a gitleaks fingerprint (<commit>:<file>:<rule>:<line>).
# Fingerprints are commit-scoped: they suppress only the exact finding in
# that commit, so a real secret added later would still be caught.
#
# ─── Test fixture: EC P-256 JWT key in vitest.config.ts ──────────────────────
# The vitest.config.ts path is already covered by the [allowlist] paths rule
# in .gitleaks.toml. Add commit-specific fingerprints here if any gitleaks
# findings survive the path allowlist (e.g. test/global-setup.ts or test/setup.ts
# if they embed the same key material).
